Date of invoice
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The date on which the card account is calculated and the balance due is
invoiced. Invoices are issued at least once a month if there have been
any movements on the card account. The date of invoice will always be a
bank day.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
Due date
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The last timely date of payment for the balance due, which has been
invoiced at the end of a collection period. The earliest due date
possible will be the first bank day of the month following the date of
invoice.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
