:FED.
2.9. Your responsibility in the event of misuse of your card
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
2.9.1 In the event that the card has been misused by another person,
&BANKNAVN. will cover the loss unless said loss is covered by Articles
2.9.2-2.9.6. It is &BANKNAVN. that must prove that the loss is covered by
Articles 2.9.1-2.9.6.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.9.2 If your card and PIN code have been misused by another person, you
will be required to cover losses of up to DKK 1,100. You will not be
required to pay more than DKK 1,100 in total if several of your cards with
the same PIN code are misused in connection with the same incident.
However, this is conditional upon you blocking all cards at the same time.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.9.3 You will be required to cover losses up to DKK 8,000 in the event
that your card has been misused by another person and the PIN code has
been used, and
.of 5mm
-¤you have failed to inform &BANKNAVN. without delay after realising that
you had lost your card, or that unauthorised persons had become aware of
the associated code,
.of
.of 5mm
-¤you have disclosed the code to the person who carried out the
unauthorised use, and you did not realise - or could not reasonably have
been expected to realise - that there was a risk of misuse, or
.of
.of 5mm
-¤you have facilitated the unauthorised use through grossly irresponsible
behaviour.
.of
.sp 3mm
In total, you must pay a maximum of 8,000 Danish kroner if more of your
cards with the same PIN code have been exploited fraudulently in connection
with the same event. This, however, implies that all cards with the same
PIN code have been blocked at the same time.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.9.4 You will be required to cover losses up to DKK 8,000 in the event
that your card has been misused by another person, when your card has
been read physically or electronically, and the unauthorised person has
used a false signature in connection with the use, and
.of 5mm
-¤that you or a party to whom you have transferred the card, have failed
to inform &BANKNAVN. without undue delay after becoming aware that the
card had been lost, or
.of
.of 5mm
-¤you or any other person to whom you have given the card has facilitated
the unauthorised use through grossly irresponsible behaviour.
.of
.sp 3mm
Your total liability cannot exceed DKK 8,000 even if you are held
liable pursuant to both Article 2.9.3 and Article 2.9.4.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
You will not be required to pay more than DKK 8,000 in total if several
of your cards with the same PIN code have been misused in connection
with the same incident.
However, this is conditional upon you blocking all cards with the same
PIN code at the same time.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.9.5 You will be held liable for the full amount if your PIN code has
been used in connection with the misuse under the following conditions:
.of 5mm
-¤You have revealed the PIN code to the person who misused the card and
realised or should have realised that there was a risk of misuse.
.of
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.9.6 You will also be held liable for the full amount if you have acted
fraudulently or have intentionally failed to fulfil your
obligations according to the regulations, including keeping the
card and the mobile phone for MasterCard SecureCode in a safe
place(see clause 2.3), protecting the PIN code (see clause 2.4) or
blocking the card (see clause 2.8).
.kp off
.kp on
.sp 3mm
2.9.7 If you use the same PIN code for multiple cards, the unlimited
liability applies to each card that has been misused.
.kp off
.kp on
.sp 3mm
2.9.8 You are not responsible for losses that occur after &BANKNAVN. has
been informed that the card is to be blocked. Nor will you be held liable
for losses if you have been unable to block your card due to circumstances
at &BANKNAVN..
.kp off
.kp on
.sp 3mm
:FED.
2.10. &BANKNAVN.'s rights and responsibility
:SKRSLUT.
.br
&BANKNAVN. is entitled to block use of your card
.of 5mm
-¤if the account to which your card is linked is closed, or
.of
.of 5mm
-¤if you breach the card terms and conditions, including running up an
overdraft on the account to which the card is associated, or
.of
.of 5mm
-¤if the card has been misused by a third party or if such misuse is
suspected.
.of
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
In the event of an overdraft, you will receive a written reminder to
clear the overdraft before your card is blocked. It may be necessary to
block the card immediately, however, in the event of particularly
serious and/or repeated overdrafts.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
When &BANKNAVN. has blocked the card, you will be informed and the
reason for and time of the blocking will be specified.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
&BANKNAVN. may also demand the return of all physical
cards that have been issued
to the account and delete all virtual cards.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS8.
:FED.
2.5. Checking account movements
:SKRSLUT.
.br
You are obliged to check the movements on your account on an ongoing
basis. If you discover any transactions which do not match your
receipts or which you believe have not been made by you, you must
contact &BANKNAVN. without undue delay. In this context, be aware of
the deadlines stated in Articles 2.6 and 2.7. In connection with your
ongoing checks of the movements on your account, note that when you
use your card to make purchases on the Internet or via mail/telephone
order, the business you deal with should not debit the sum from your
account until the goods in question have been shipped. However, when
you book airline tickets or concert tickets, the company will normally
debit the amount as soon as you book the travel or order the tickets.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.6. Reversing payments you have approved
.sp 3mm
If you did not know the final sum when approving the transaction.
:SKRSLUT.
.br
If you did not know the final sum when you approved the payment, and if
the sum subsequently debited from your account is significantly higher
than what you could reasonably have expected, you may be entitled to
reverse the payment. This may, for example, occur in connection with
renting a car or checking out from a hotel, when you have allowed the
business or hotel to debit your account for refuelling the vehicle or
restocking the mini-bar.
